	<str name="Title">
		Portable computer having secondary display
	</str>
	<str name="Abstract">
		A portable computer having improved capabilities for facilitating a demonstration to an audience. The computer's main display is pivotably mounted to the keyboard portion of the computer, allowing an audience to view the computer's output. A secondary liquid crystal display is mounted on or near the computer's keyboard, allowing the computer's operator to view the computer's output when the screen is facing the audience. The secondary liquid crystal display can also be operated independently of the main display in order to prolong screen and battery life.
	</str>
